summary: I’m really really proud of my progress! I have been going to the gym on average three days a week for lifting and cardio. This...
body: I’m really really proud of my progress! I have been going to the gym on average three days a week for lifting and cardio. This has been about two years in the making for me. I was extremely inconsistent that first year but have been steadily gaining muscle. I am now at 150, and struggling to see that number on the scale. People are so judgmental about weight but it’s truly just a number. I keep reminding myself that this number growing is actually a better change for my body because I am trading up with muscle mass. I am thankful for the body I have and that I am finally beginning to treat it with respect.

caption:
I was ugly laughing cause the girl froze because I was taking a pic. Lol. #wahmlife yo.
.
.
I posted this to show we have a busy life, but we still keep it #healthy yo. While teaching the kids and trying to get this business up and running; you would think I would let stuff fly by. I ain’t gonna lie. Ive thought about it. Ok. Struggled.
.
.
But I keep going. I drink my @ancientnutrition shake during #homeschool, I teach the kids, I tweet, I insta, I fb, when I can. I know it’s not perfect but hey it’s where God has me. And I’m good.
.
.
I may not be perfect or look perfect or act perfect (#awkwardmomlife) but I trust in the Lord to guide me through.
.
.
What am I saying? Never give up friend. Keep on trucking and keep your goals - whatever they are - in your mind. Be kind to yourself and? Take one day at a time.
.
.
You got this.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

You are perfect the way you are and your body is beautiful and elegant and graceful no matter what number is on the scale. I love you xx
